description:
Captain Guy Gruters was a fighter pilot during the Vietnam War and flew over 400 combat missions. He was shot down in 1967 and spent the next 5 years in POW camps, including the notorious &quot;Hanoi Hilton&quot;. In this talk, he relates the incredible experiences of his capture and shares a unique message of how his faith and hope sustained him. He has been married for over 40 years and has 7 children.

